\begin_layout Subsection
Target Audience
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Our music streaming platform will have the opportunity to be deployed in
 various home networks, college networks, and perhaps even radio stations.
 The target audience is mainly students and home owners who will be able
 to appreciate the simplicity of the system.
 Radio stations will definitely find it useful, but it will need some feature
 additions for them to fully exploit the software's power.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Some other similar products
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are some other servers like SHOUTcast and Icecast that address the
 same needs but SHOUTcast is a proprietary one and Icecast is open source
 but hard to setup and maintain and there have been no recent updates to
 it.
 In addition, both are meant for streaming as a two-way thing.
 Both servers accept the input also as a stream, which means the user has
 to setup some other tool which streams music from their hard disk to the
 server.
 While the feature is an advantage for those doing live shows etc.
 where live digital audio can directly be streamed, it complicates setup
 for simply streaming existing content.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Legal feasibility
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Legal feasibility is the determination of any infringement, violation, or
 liability that could result from development of the system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We are not responsible if any entity chooses to stream pirated music using
 our server.
 It is the sole responsibility of the concerned entity to ensure that streamed
 music is procured legally and it is not transgressing any laws of the country
 where it is situated.
 It is to be noted that legal music, streamed over an internal network to
 a small group of users, who DO NOT SAVE IT, is considered acceptable under
 most copyright laws.
 Users who want to run publicly available stations will of course have to
 acquire relevant rights to all music, which varies from region to region.
\end_layout

